rat believes that this situation impoverishes our ability to see the complex relations of law, culture, and society in all their variety and to connect theorizing about law with its application in the humanities and social sciences. The contributors to this book aim to assess the place of legal scholarship in the liberal arts by asking whether and how legal research and pedagogy are different in liberal arts settings than they are in law schools.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aEducation, HumanisticzUnited States. 0aLawxStudy and teaching (Higher)zUnited States. 4aEducation & History Of Education. 4aHistory. 4aLegal History & Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAbramson, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBybee, Keith J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConstable, Marianne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, J. Douglas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHartog, Hendrik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSage Heinzelman, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarat, Austin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarat, Austin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSilbey, Susan S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWhite, James Boyd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172984340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501729843423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501729843/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Co